fields.description:
Viewport row model expansion? It's very powerful, but not documented greatly, really need a real world end to end example. Maybe a streaming database like RethinkDB would be good?

Enterprise Row Model expansion? How does it connect to real world databases other than standard relational databases.

Server sides to consider:
+ Apache Spark integration
+ RethinkDB

==== START From Andrew Clancy emails:

eg a jupyter notebook/lab widget: https://github.com/quantopian/qgrid
and Plotly dash / shinyR? 

----

"Yup - our data science platform has Spark at it's core (as did QuantumBlacks) - it's all part of the whole data science/quant world, and Jupyter is another key player - the defacto IDE for most data scientists (vs RStudio).

Juptyter/Plotly Dash & shinyR arent really server integrations per-se - they'd each be a fairly trivial client-side wrapper around the grid. "

https://shiny.rstudio.com/articles/building-outputs.html
https://plot.ly/dash/plugins
https://jupyter-notebook.readthedocs.io/en/latest/extending/index.html

------

Yep - on a few minutes reflection (over standup), this is exactly what you need to do to 'integrate with spark' - spark is a server technology, these are some the common UIs/IDEs used by data scientists & quants while interacting with it. Jupyter would be the biggest win, but they're all trivial, and as slickgrid is has just got in there (which as we've discussed you're a lot better than) you have a big opportunity to get ahead of the wave & open yourself more to the whole of the data science/python/R & Spark (and scala) communities.

==== END From Andrew Clancy emails:
